COMMODITY
  Show commodity stockpiles and delivery/distribution settings.

SYNTAX
  commodity [<sects>]
  comm      [<sects>]

DESCRIPTION
  Lists every commodity held in each owned sector, plus delivery
  and distribution direction settings for each item.

  Delivery/distribution columns use one character per commodity:
    s=shell  g=gun  p=petrol  i=iron  d=dust  b=bar
    o=oil    l=lcm  h=hcm     r=rad
  A dot (.) means no delivery set.  $ means deliver to dist center.

  Commodity abbreviations:
    c=civ  m=mil  u=uw   f=food  s=shell  g=gun  p=petrol
    i=iron d=dust b=bar  o=oil   l=lcm    h=hcm  r=rad

EXAMPLE
  commodity *               all sectors
  commodity 5,-1            just the LCM factory

